{
  "name": "Pharma HITL Review — Telegram",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## HITL Entity Review via Telegram\n\n**What it does:** serves uncertain entity-resolution pairs from the `hitl_review_queue` data table to a reviewer on Telegram, one at a time, with Merge / Separate buttons. Decisions are written back and the next pair is sent automatically.\n\n### Setup (one time)\n1. Create a bot with **@BotFather**, copy the token\n2. Create a **Telegram API credential** in n8n with that token\n3. Attach the credential to the 3 Telegram nodes\n4. Activate the workflow\n5. Send **/review** to your bot to start\n\nQueue is pre-sorted by revenue impact — highest-stakes pairs come first. Price-based suggestions appear in the card when available.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 460
      },
      "id": "note1",
      "name": "Setup Notes",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1600,
        -416
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "id": "trg",
      "name": "Telegram Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.telegramTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        -1088,
        16
      ],
      "webhookId": "27bc4789-cf68-400d-935a-2ec46dffaa6c"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Standardize trigger payload: button tap (decision) or chat command\nconst u = $input.first().json;\nif (u.callback_query) {\n  const [pairId, decision] = String(u.callback_query.data || '').split('|');\n  return [{ json: {\n    kind: 'decision',\n    chat_id: u.callback_query.message.chat.id,\n    query_id: u.callback_query.id,\n    pair_id: Number(pairId),\n    decision: decision || 'SKIP',\n  }}];\n}\nreturn [{ json: {\n  kind: 'command',\n  chat_id: u.message.chat.id,\n  text: (u.message.text || '').trim(),\n}}];"
      },
      "id": "norm",
      "name": "Normalize Update",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -800,
        -16
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "version": 2,
            "leftValue": "",
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "typeValidation": "loose"
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "c1",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.kind === 'decision' }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "true",
                "singleValue": true
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "isdec",
      "name": "Is Decision?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [
        -560,
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "callback",
        "queryId": "={{ $('Normalize Update').first().json.query_id }}",
        "additionalFields": {
          "text": "={{ 'Saved: ' + $('Normalize Update').first().json.decision }}"
        }
      },
      "id": "ack",
      "name": "Ack Button",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.telegram",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        -336,
        -160
      ],
      "webhookId": "d6b86504-9684-41e7-8f54-176def8a1e2a",
